cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT 

This paper is about using evolutionary algorithms to automatically design neural network architectures for image classification problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on image classification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the models, which is a common concern in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of evolutionary algorithms also falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the computational requirements, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as well.
